<h2 class=3D"classyunicodedone">Understanding the Conversion Formulas</h2>
<div style=3D"margin-bottom: 30px;">
<div style=3D"background-color: #f8f8f8; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-=
radius: 5px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
<h4 style=3D"font-size: 18px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #3=
33;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">FPS to MPH Formula</h4>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom: 0;">To convert from feet per second to miles per=
 hour, multiply the FPS value by 0.6818181818. This is because there are 5,=
280 feet in a mile and 3,600 seconds in an hour, so the conversion factor i=
s (3600 =C3=B7 5280) =3D 0.6818.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 10px;"><strong>MPH =3D FPS =C3=97=
 0.6818</strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 10px;">Example: A bullet travelin=
g at 1000 FPS is moving at 681.8 MPH.</p>
</div>
<div style=3D"background-color: #f8f8f8; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-=
radius: 5px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">
<h4 style=3D"font-size: 18px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #3=
33;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">MPH to FPS Formula</h4>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom: 0;">To convert from miles per hour to feet per s=
econd, divide the MPH value by 0.6818181818, or more simply, multiply by 1.=
4667.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 10px;"><strong>FPS =3D MPH =C3=B7=
 0.6818</strong> or <strong>FPS =3D MPH =C3=97 1.4667</strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 10px;">Example: A velocity of 681=
.82 MPH equals approximately 1000 FPS.</p>
</div>
</div>
