oll down to view comprehensive conversion charts for quick reference.</li>
</ol></div>
<h3 style=3D"font-size: 22px; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; color:=
 #333; font-weight: 500;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">Why Convert Between F=
PS and MPH</h3>
<div style=3D"display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 30p=
x;">
<div style=3D"flex: 1; min-width: 300px; background-color: #f8f8f8; border:=
 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius: 5px; padding: 20px;">
<h4 style=3D"font-size: 18px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px; color: #3=
33;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">For Ballistics Analysis</h4>
<p>Manufacturers typically list ammunition velocity in FPS, but comparing t=
his to familiar speeds in MPH helps visualize just how fast bullets actuall=
y travel.</p>
</div>
<div style=3D"flex: 1; min-width: 300px; background-color: #f8f8f8; border:=
 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius: 5px; padding: 20px;">
<h4 style=3D"font-size: 18px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px; color: #3=
33;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">For Equipment Specifications</h4>
<p>Some shooting and chronograph equipment may display results in different=
 units. This converter allows you to standardize your measurements.</p>
</div>
<div style=3D"flex: 1; min-width: 300px; background-color: #f8f8f8; border:=
 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius: 5px; padding: 20px;">
<h4 style=3D"font-size: 18px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px; color: #3=
33;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">For Educational Purposes</h4>
<p>Understanding bullet velocity in both units provides perspective. For ex=
ample, a standard 9mm round traveling at 1200 FPS is moving at about 818 MP=
H=E2=80=94faster than many commercial airplanes!</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 style=3D"font-size: 22px; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; color:=
 #333; font-weight: 500;" class=3D"classyunicodedone">Typical Ammunition Ve=
locities</h3>
<div style=3D"background-color: #f8f8f8; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-=
radius: 5px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
<ul style=3D"padding-left: 20px; margin: 0;">
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Pistol Ammunition:</strong> Typi=
cally ranges from 750-1400 FPS (511-955 MPH)</li>
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Rifle Ammunition:</strong> Typic=
ally ranges from 2000-4000 FPS (1364-2727 MPH)</li>
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Rimfire Ammunition:</strong> Typ=
